title: Government announces appointments to Expert Committee on Food Safety
content_text:
p>
	The Government announced today (September 12) the re-appointment of 
	Professor Ma Ching-yung as the Chairman of the Expert Committee on Food 
	Safety and the appointment of a serving member, Professor Chen Zhen-yu, as 
	the Vice-Chairman of the Expert Committee. At the same time, the appointment of five new members and re-appointment of 
	13 incumbent members to the Expert Committee were announced. All the appointments are for a term of two years with effect from September

15, 2014. Four new members are local representatives. They are Dr Lawrence Chan, 
	Professor Leo Sin Yat-ming, Professor Chris Wong Kong-chu and Dr Raymond 
	Wong Siu-ming. A new overseas member, Professor Steve Hathaway, is also 
	appointed. Dr Chan has been a veterinarian with the Hong Kong Jockey Club. He served as 
	the chairman of the Ethics Committee, Veterinary Surgeon Board, from 2006 to 
	2012 as well as the Veterinary Services Manager at equestrian events of the

2012 as well as the Veterinary Services Manager at equestrian events of the 
	Guangzhou Asian Games in 2010. Professor Sin teaches at the Department of Marketing, Chinese University of 
	Hong Kong. He is an expert in strategic marketing and cross-cultural 
	consumer behaviour. Professor Wong is the Head of the Department of Biology, Hong Kong Baptist 
	University. His expertise also includes environmental contamination and 
	toxicology. Dr Wong is the Consultant of the Department of Medicine and Therapeutics, 
	Prince of Wales Hospital, and has served at its Poison Treatment Centre

Prince of Wales Hospital, and has served at its Poison Treatment Centre 
	since 2005.  Professor Hathaway is currently Director, Science and Risk Assessment, in 
	New Zealand's Ministry for Primary Industries. With an early academic career 
	in veterinary epidemiology and public health, he later specialised in food 
	safety risk analysis and has had extensive involvement in national and 
	international regulatory matters including chairing the Codex Committee on 
	Milk and Milk Products, and working with Codex, the World Organisation for

Milk and Milk Products, and working with Codex, the World Organisation for 
	Animal Health, the Food and Agriculture Organization and the World Health 
	Organization in the area of food safety. The Secretary for Food and Health, Dr Ko Wing-man, welcomed the new members 
	and those re-appointed to the Expert Committee. He said the community looks 
	forward to benefiting from their wise counsel to the Director of Food and 
	Environmental Hygiene on strategic and operational aspects of different food

Environmental Hygiene on strategic and operational aspects of different food 
	safety issues. Dr Ko also thanked the outgoing members - Mr Allen Ho, Dr Michael Lam, Dr 
	Matthew Ng, Dr Albert Chan and Dr Paul Brent from Australia - for their 
	valuable contributions to the work of the Expert Committee during their term 
	of appointment. The Expert Committee advises the Director of Food and Environmental Hygiene 
	on existing or new food safety operational strategies and measures to 
	protect public health. It also sets standards/guidelines relating to food

protect public health. It also sets standards/guidelines relating to food safety and food composition having regard to international practices, trends and developments. Following is the membership list of the Expert Committee as from September 15, 2014: Chairman: Professor Ma Ching-yung
